# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CODEOWNERS — collaboration governance for sqd-milestone
#
# How this works: when "Require review from Code Owners" is enabled in branch
# protection, any PR that changes a path below cannot merge without an approval
# from the listed owner. This is the approval queue.
#
# Ownership is by DOMAIN, not just existing files. A folder line (e.g.
# /src/components/srp/) owns everything in that folder — INCLUDING files that
# don't exist yet — so a director can add new components, features, and whole
# new tools inside their lane without extra permission. They only hit Ashley's
# review when a change reaches OUTSIDE their domain (e.g. a route in App.tsx).
#
# PLACEHOLDERS: swap @SPENCER_GH for the real GitHub username once Spencer
# accepts the repo invite. Until then the catch-all `*` line routes anything
# Spencer touches to @churchwebsquad — safe by default.
